DUSG

NAME
  dusg -- generate a static site

SYNOPSIS
  dusg --src='./your-source-directory' --dest='./your-destination-directory' --template='./your-template.js'

DESCRIPTION
  The dusg command creates a static site from an input directory of markdown files and a JavaScript template.

  The options are as follows:

  -s, --src=directory
    Source directory of markdown files to use to generate the site.

  -d, --dest=directory
    Output directory of the static site.

  -t, --template=file
    A JavaScript module with a default export that will receive the static site data object.

  -h, --help
    Show this document.

  -v, --version
    Show the version number.

  --clean-urls
    Places each file in its own directory so './src/about-me.md/' would become './dest/about-me/index.html'. Defaults to true.

  --extension
    Changes the output file extension. The default is '.html'.

  --html-key
    Key to use in the static site generator object for the markdown parsed as html. The default is 'html'.

  --metadata-key
    Key to use in the static site generator object for the metadata parsed as YAML. The default is 'metadata'.

  --files-key
    Key to use in the static site generator object for the array of source files. The default is 'files'.

